    "VICTORIA": "A genus of aquatic plants named in honor of Queen Victoria. TheVictoria regia is a native of Guiana and Brazil. Its large, spreadingleaves are often over five feet in diameter, and have a rim fromthree to five inches high; its immense rose-white flowers sometimesattain a diameter of nearly two feet.",
    "VICTORIA CRAPE": "A kind of cotton crape.",
    "VICTORIAN": "Of or pertaining to the reign of Queen Victoria of England; as,the Victorian poets. Victorian period. See Dionysian period, underDyonysian.",
